---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>
			<h1>Peak Rock<br /> Communication Services</h1>

			<p>
				My name is Alister, and I am a vanlifer, with 15 years of experience in the telecommunications and networking world. Due to my lifestyle, I am uniquely placed to reach all areas of the UK and Europe in order to assist people with overhauling and renewing their network infrastructure. <br />
				<br />
				I offer new installation and refurbishment of existing networks.
			</p>

			<section id="services" class="offerings">
				<h2>What I Offer</h2>

				<details>
					<summary>Customised Network Solutions</summary>
					<p>
						Tailored network solutions for homes, businesses and unusual environments, designed around your actual needs rather than off-the-shelf assumptions.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Existing Network Testing and Auditing</summary>
					<p>
						Testing, auditing and reviewing existing infrastructure so you can understand what is in place, what has changed over time, and where problems are likely to arise.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Problem Solving</summary>
					<p>
						Bespoke fault finding and infrastructure planning aimed at solving the root cause of network issues rather than applying temporary fixes.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>CCTV</summary>
					<p>
						Wired CCTV infrastructure planned and installed with proper cabling standards for reliability, clarity and long-term maintainability.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>POS</summary>
					<p>
						Practical network and cabling solutions for card machines, tills and retail systems so everyday trading is not disrupted by avoidable faults.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>121 Service</summary>
					<p>
						Direct one-to-one service from survey through to implementation, with no account managers, handoffs or company-policy nonsense in the middle.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>WiFi Solutions</summary>
					<p>
						WiFi design and improvement for homes, hospitality, rural sites and busy environments where plug-and-play kit does not deliver what is needed.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Structured Cabling</summary>
					<p>
						High-quality structured cabling designed to proper standards, making your infrastructure easier to use, maintain and expand in future.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>First Fix Consultancy</summary>
					<p>
						Planning network infrastructure at the right stage of a build so connectivity is considered before the walls are finished and the options are limited.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Final Fix and Implementation</summary>
					<p>
						Final-stage installation, termination, testing and bring-up work to make sure the finished system is live, labelled and working as intended.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>PBX / Phone Systems</summary>
					<p>
						Practical phone system design and setup for homes, offices and small business sites, whether replacing older systems or starting fresh.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Guest WiFi Networks</summary>
					<p>
						Guest WiFi designed to be easy for visitors to use while staying properly separated from the main network.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Internet Failover & Backup Connectivity</summary>
					<p>
						Backup connectivity planning so a broadband failure does not stop the whole site from working.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Starlink & 4G/5G Installations</summary>
					<p>
						Alternative internet solutions for rural, mobile or difficult locations where fixed-line services are limited or unreliable.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Outbuilding & Multi-Building Connectivity</summary>
					<p>
						Reliable connections between houses, annexes, offices, barns, workshops and other external buildings.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Smart Devices & IoT Networking</summary>
					<p>
						Network setups that properly support smart devices and connected systems without turning the whole environment into a management headache.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Remote Access & Monitoring Setup</summary>
					<p>
						Sensible remote access and monitoring options so systems are easier to support, understand and maintain.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Hospitality & Airbnb Networking</summary>
					<p>
						Network design for guest-facing environments where reliability, simplicity and repeatable performance matter.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Network Documentation & Handover</summary>
					<p>
						Clear documentation, labelling and handover information so you are not left guessing how your own infrastructure works.
					</p>
				</details>
			</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 100%;
		padding: 1.5rem 2rem 5rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		line-height: 1.05;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.offerings {
		max-width: 950px;
		margin: 2.5rem auto 0;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.offerings h2 {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
	}

	.offerings details {
		border: 1px solid #ccc;
		border-radius: 6px;
		background: white;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.offerings summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.offerings summary::after {
		content: "+";
		float: right;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.offerings details[open] summary::after {
		content: "−";
	}

	.offerings details p {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0 1.1rem 1rem;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
		text-align: left;
		max-width: none;
	}
</style>